<|startoftext|>Question:Why is there no way to know what the future of my life is?
Answer:It's very difficult to determine if it will last forever, or not to stay with you. There are some that feel that it might be impossible to move on; I'm very happy with the situation that I found myself in.  But I can only imagine what I could have accomplished with my life, and I'm still learning to live the way I want to today. I could have been a grown man but that's not what I wanted. I'd have been able to be able to walk up to you, hug you, talk to you, touch you, put you in a room, and say hello once again. Life is long, stressful, but that's what I want. I'm still learning. If I lived what I have, I would have done many things for people that have been in this life or had a life that has brought them happiness. It seems this doesn't apply to the rest of us. What does? How can you know? 

Life is always changing all the time and is always changing. Your future is in your hands, whether it's in the past, for better or worse, if not... but the people in your life will always want to see you moving on and making you happy. People do that. I wish you all the best.

It has taken many, many years, and still people don't like to live in it. They don't have the tools to deal with it and have the courage to try. That is why it's so difficult and sometimes even impossible for an experienced person to take responsibility. 

So maybe you need a change. Maybe you've gotten something from your life, something that you can live your life with and never forget. 

I think it's important to let go, not leave it. You've lost a lot of time, but have you lost something? A year or two is not all you have. You're still growing, but the change in your life is not good, it doesn't seem to you, just now. Some people are going through something that has hurt them more than most, but the feeling just isn't there... 

Hope this helps.

You will be missed.<|endoftext|>
